HEADWORD: Reposal
<hw>Re*pos"al</hw> <pr>(r⟦esl⟧*p⟦omac⟧z"⟦ait⟧l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[From <er>Repose</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act or state of
reposing; <as>as, the <ex>reposal</ex> of a trust</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That on which one reposes.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Burton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Reposance</ent>⟦br⟧
